content.description: Start on jugs on the left face. Traverse around and under to the horn undercling. Power swing/slap (or use intermediary crimps) to gain the right hand arête. Work up the arête with opposition until the huge jugs leading to the top.
content.protection: Crashpad. There are some ugly rocks under the overhang.
content.location: West (right) at the beach. Less than .5 miles. Second of 2 obvious roofs on the right is the "Spinal Roof"

content.description: Start on jugs on far left. Same as Thoracic Shart. Traverse via finger locks in the horizontal crack under roof. Pull around right roof lip. Lock off finger lock and power up to the jugs.
content.protection: Crashpad. Ugly rocks under the "Spinal Roof"
content.location: West (right) at the beach. Less than .5 miles. Second of 2 obvious roofs is the "Spinal Roof"
